## Session Overview

This session completed the physical prototype for the Melbourne Metro Health Network (MMHN). All three campus routers were verified and connected in a hub-and-spoke topology. VLAN segmentation was configured on all three Cisco Catalyst switches via console cable. Security hardening was applied to all TP-Link routers. Windows Firewall rules were added to the ACS VM to mirror the ACL design from the Packet Tracer simulation. Inter-campus routing was confirmed with successful pings between the CBD VM and both Clayton and Mernda routers.

---

## 1. Mernda Router — IP Configuration and Verification

The Mernda campus TP-Link router was the final router to be configured this session. The router was reset to factory default (192.168.0.1) and the LAN IP was changed to 192.168.12.1 via the admin panel. The laptop was set to DHCP, which assigned 192.168.12.100 automatically after the router rebooted.

Ping test confirmed 0% packet loss:

```
