## 2. Hub-and-Spoke Topology Connected

Physical connections established as per the MMHN design:

- Wall outlet → CBD TP-Link (WAN port)
- Clayton TP-Link WAN port → CBD LAN port
- Mernda TP-Link WAN port → CBD LAN port
- Each TP-Link LAN → Cisco Catalyst 3560-CX switch → end device

This mirrors the hub-and-spoke design from the logical network diagram and the Packet Tracer simulation.

---

## 3. Security Hardening — All Three TP-Link Routers

Security hardening was applied to all three TP-Link routers via the admin panel. The following changes were made on each router:

- Admin password changed from default to a strong password
- WPA2-PSK with AES encryption enabled on both 2.4GHz and 5GHz bands
- SSID renamed per campus: CBD campus, Clayton campus, Mernda campus
- Remote management disabled

![TP-Link CBD Campus Wireless Settings — WPA2-PSK, AES, SSID: CBD campus](evidence/tp_link_CBD_campus.png)

