## 4. Windows Firewall Rules — ACS VM (CBD Campus)

Windows Firewall rules were added to the ACS VM on the CBD campus to mirror the ACL rules from the Packet Tracer simulation. Rules were applied using `netsh advfirewall` in an elevated Command Prompt.

Rules added:
- Block Guest subnet (192.168.40.0/24) from reaching Admin (192.168.10.0/24)
- Block Guest subnet (192.168.40.0/24) from reaching Clinical (192.168.20.0/24)
- Block IoT subnet (192.168.30.0/24) from reaching Clinical (192.168.20.0/24)

Verification command output:

```
Rule Name:    Block IoT to Clinical     Action: Block
Rule Name:    Block Guest to Clinical   Action: Block
Rule Name:    Block Guest to Admin      Action: Block
```

![Windows Firewall rules confirmed — three block rules active](evidence/firewall_block.png)

