## 8. Inter-Campus Connectivity — Ping Tests

From the ACS Windows VM on the CBD campus, pings were sent to both Clayton and Mernda routers to verify inter-campus routing through the hub-and-spoke topology.

```
ping 192.168.12.1 (Mernda router)
Reply from 192.168.12.1: bytes=32 time=42ms TTL=249
Reply from 192.168.12.1: bytes=32 time=42ms TTL=249
Reply from 192.168.12.1: bytes=32 time=42ms TTL=249
Reply from 192.168.12.1: bytes=32 time=42ms TTL=249
Packets: Sent = 4, Received = 4, Lost = 0 (0% loss)

ping 192.168.11.1 (Clayton router)
Reply from 192.168.11.1: bytes=32 time=37ms TTL=249
Reply from 192.168.11.1: bytes=32 time=39ms TTL=249
Reply from 192.168.11.1: bytes=32 time=37ms TTL=249
Reply from 192.168.11.1: bytes=32 time=37ms TTL=249
Packets: Sent = 4, Received = 4, Lost = 0 (0% loss)
```

Both spoke campus routers reachable from the CBD hub with 0% packet loss. TTL of 249 confirms traffic is routing through multiple hops as expected in the hub-and-spoke design.

