## 9. Known Limitations

**End-to-end device pings:** Direct pings between end devices across campuses (e.g. Clayton PC to Mernda PC) return destination unreachable. This is due to NAT on the consumer TP-Link routers. Resolving this would require static routes configured on the CBD router's admin panel or replacing TP-Link routers with enterprise routing equipment. This is documented as a hardware constraint rather than a design flaw — the Packet Tracer simulation demonstrates full end-to-end connectivity under enterprise conditions.

**VLAN enforcement across campuses:** VLAN segmentation is enforced at the switch level within each campus. Cross-campus VLAN traffic separation relies on ACL rules (implemented via Windows Firewall on the VM) rather than inter-campus switch trunking, which would require enterprise-grade inter-switch connections.

